      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Former Victorian CAN BE A RUEBE NZ (6) made a good start for the new yard when she came from a wider barrier and finished 2.8 metres away in third in a higher-graded race at this circuit and distance. Hart sticks and she could be hard to stop in this suitable assignment. RIVERA LOU (7) is first up from a spell of three months but flies fresh having won all three resuming efforts. Expect him to be wound up again. Big chance. MISTER MANAGER (1) drew widest but worked to the front and boxed on to finish midfield here last week so is better served by the ace draw. TOORAM CEE CEE (8) draws wide but has been good in two starts so far this campaign, coming from the back line to score fresh then racing three wide without cover but sticking on for a 2m second here last week.",
